issue_body:
when an invalid media type is used on content-type or Accept header but with compatible-with parameter an exception is thrown which is not handled and emits a WARN log message
nothing is returned to a server

reproduce:
```
curl --request PUT \
  --url 'http://localhost:9200/my_index1?include_type_name=true' \
  --header 'Accept: aaa/bbb' \
  --header 'Authorization: Basic ZWxhc3RpYzpwYXNzd29yZA==' \
  --header 'Content-Type: aaa/bbb;compatible-with=7' \
  --data '{
    "mappings": {
        "type1": {
            "properties": {
                "location": {
                    "type": "geo_shape"
                }
            }
        }
    }
}'
```

we should handle this exception and return something meaning full to a user

I have a feeling that it might have been discussed already.  @jakelandis @joegallo do you remember? any thoughts?

**Elasticsearch version** (`bin/elasticsearch --version`): 7.15.1

**OS version** (`uname -a` if on a Unix-like system): cloud

**Description of the problem including expected versus actual behavior**: I upgraded my cluster from 6.8.19->6.8.20->7.15.1.
Now when I try to create a filter - Kibana filter panel doesn't display values. 

Please note this works fine on a fresh 7.15.1.

<img width="1792" alt="Screen Shot 2021-10-14 at 5 46 48 PM" src="https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/7074629/137400116-cc1d9908-c758-4a8e-8ae0-b825da0ad563.png">


In the console - posting this:
```
